\par
\b\i CSS Transitions\b0\i0\par
To create a transition effect, you must specify two things:\par
the CSS property you want to add an effect to\par
the duration of the effect\par
Note: If the duration part is not specified, the transition will have no effect, because the default value is 0.\par
The following example shows a 100px * 100px red <div> element. The <div> element has also specified a transition effect for the width property, with a duration of 2 seconds:\par
\b Example1\cf3\b0\par

\pard\li2160\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b div \{\par
  width: 100px;\par
  height: 100px;\par
  background: red;\par
  transition: width 2s;\par
\}\par
div:hover \{\par
  width: 300px;\par
\}\lang9\par

\pard\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0 EXAMPLE 2\b0\par

\pard\li2160\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf3\b .btn \{\par
  background-color: #ddd;\par
  border: none;\par
  color: black;\par
  padding: 16px 32px;\par
  text-align: center;\par
  font-size: 16px;\par
  margin: 4px 2px;\par
  transition: 0.3s;\par
\}\par
\par
.btn:hover \{\par
  background-color: #3e8e41;\par
  color: white;\par
\}\par

\pard\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\b0\par
\par
\par
\par
\b\fs32 Change Several Property Values\b0\fs22\par
The following example adds a transition effect for both the width and height property, with a duration of 2 seconds for the width and 4 seconds for the height:\par
\par

\pard\li2160\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf3\b Example\par
div \{\par
  transition: width 2s, height 4s;\par
\}\par
div:hover \{\par
  width: 300px;\par
  height: 300px;\par
\}\par

\pard\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\b0\par
\b\fs28 Specify the Speed Curve of the Transition\b0\fs22\par
The transition-timing-function property specifies the speed curve of the transition effect.\par
\par
The transition-timing-function property can have the following values:\par
\par
ease - specifies a transition effect with a slow start, then fast, then end slowly (this is default)\par
linear - specifies a transition effect with the same speed from start to end\par
ease-in - specifies a transition effect with a slow start\par
ease-out - specifies a transition effect with a slow end\par
ease-in-out - specifies a transition effect with a slow start and end\par
cubic-bezier(n,n,n,n) - lets you define your own values in a cubic-bezier function\par
The following example shows the some of the different speed curves that can be used:\par
\par
Example\par

\pard\li1440\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf3\b #div1 \{transition-timing-function: linear;\}\par
#div2 \{transition-timing-function: ease;\}\par
#div3 \{transition-timing-function: ease-in;\}\par
#div4 \{transition-timing-function: ease-out;\}\par
#div5 \{transition-timing-function: ease-in-out;\}\par

\pard\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\b0\par
\b\fs24 Delay the Transition Effect\b0\fs22\par
The transition-delay property specifies a delay (in seconds) for the transition effect.\par
\par
The following example has a 1 second delay before starting:\par
\par

\pard\li2160\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf3\b Example\par

\pard\li2880\sa200\sl276\slmult1 div \{\par
  width: 100px;\par
  height: 100px;\par
  background: red;\par
  transition: width 3s;\par
  transition-delay: 1s;\par
\}\par
\par
div:hover \{\par
  width: 300px;\par
\}\cf0\b0\par

\pard\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b\par
Another  Transition Examples\par

\pard\li2160\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf3\fs24 div \{\par
  width: 100px;\par
  height: 100px;\par
  background: red;\par
  transition-property: width;\par
  transition-duration: 2s;\par
  transition-timing-function: linear;\par
  transition-delay: 1s;\par
\}\par
\par
div:hover \{\par
  width: 300px;\par
\}\par

\pard\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\fs28 Transition + Transform\b0\fs22\par
\par
\cf3\b\fs24 <style> \par
div \{\par
  width: 100px;\par
  height: 100px;\par
  background: red;\par
  transition: width 2s, height 2s, transform 2s;\par
\}\par
\par
div:hover \{\par
  width: 300px;\par
  height: 300px;\par
  transform: rotate(180deg);\par
\}\par
</style>\par
